members.name: Jimin
members.history: Park Ji-min (Korean: 박지민; born October 13, 1995), known mononymously as Jimin, is a South Korean singer, songwriter and dancer. In 2013, he made his debut as a member of the South Korean boy band BTS, under the record label Big Hit Entertainment. Jimin has released three solo tracks under BTS name—'Lie' in 2016, 'Serendipity' in 2017, and 'Filter' in 2020—all of which have charted on South Koreas Gaon Digital Chart. He released his first credited solo song, the digital track 'Promise', which he co-wrote, in 2018 and recorded the duet 'With You' with Ha Sung-woon for the soundtrack for the TvN drama Our Blues in 2022. Jimin released his debut solo album, Face in 2023. It debuted at number one in South Korea and Japan, and number two in the United States, while its second single, 'Like Crazy', debuted at number one on the US Billboard Hot 100, making him the highest-charting Korean solo artist in history on the Billboard 200 and the Hot 100 at the time, and the first to debut atop the latter. Jimin is also the first Korean solo artist to top the Billboard Artist 100 chart.

members.name: Jungkook
members.position: Main Vocalist, Lead Dancer, Sub Rapper, Center, Maknae
members.history: Jeon Jung-kook (Korean: 전정국; RR: Jeon Jeongguk; born September 1, 1997), known mononymously as Jungkook (stylized as Jung Kook), is a South Korean singer, songwriter and dancer. He rose to prominence as a member and vocalist of the South Korean boy band BTS. He has performed three solo songs as part of BTS discography— Begin in 2016, Euphoria in 2018, and My Time in 2020—all of which charted on South Koreas Gaon Digital Chart. He also recorded the soundtrack song 'Stay Alive' for the BTS-based webtoon 7Fates: Chakho.

members.name: V
members.history: Kim Tae-hyung (Korean: 김태형; born December 30, 1995), known professionally as V (뷔), is a South Korean singer, songwriter, and a member of the boy band BTS. Since his debut with the band in 2013, V has performed three solo songs under their name—'Stigma' in 2016, 'Singularity' in 2018, and 'Inner Child' in 2020—all of which charted on South Koreas Gaon Digital Chart.

members.name: J-Hope
members.history: Jung Ho-seok (Korean: 정호석; born February 18, 1994), better known by his stage name J-Hope (stylized in lower case), is a South Korean rapper, singer-songwriter, dancer, and record producer. He made his debut as a member of South Korean boy band BTS in 2013, under Big Hit Entertainment.

members.name: Suga
members.history: Park Ji-min (Korean: 박지민; born October 13, 1995), known mononymously as Jimin, is a South Korean singer, songwriter and dancer. In 2013, he made his debut as a member of the South Korean boy band BTS, under the record label Big Hit Entertainment. Jimin has released three solo tracks under BTS name—'Lie' in 2016, 'Serendipity' in 2017, and 'Filter' in 2020—all of which have charted on South Koreas Gaon Digital Chart. He released his first credited solo song, the digital track 'Promise', which he co-wrote, in 2018 and recorded the duet 'With You' with Ha Sung-woon for the soundtrack for the TvN drama Our Blues in 2022. Jimin released his debut solo album, Face in 2023. It debuted at number one in South Korea and Japan, and number two in the United States, while its second single, 'Like Crazy', debuted at number one on the US Billboard Hot 100, making him the highest-charting Korean solo artist in history on the Billboard 200 and the Hot 100 at the time, and the first to debut atop the latter. Jimin is also the first Korean solo artist to top the Billboard Artist 100 chart.

members.name: Jin
members.history: Kim Seok-jin (Korean: 김석진; born December 4, 1992), known professionally as Jin (진), is a South Korean singer, songwriter, and member of the South Korean boy band BTS. Jin has co-written and released three solo tracks with BTS: 'Awake' in 2016, 'Epiphany' in 2018, and 'Moon' in 2020, all of which have charted on South Koreas Gaon Digital Chart. In 2019, Jin released his first independent song, the digital track Tonight. He made his official debut as a solo artist in October 2022, with the release of the single The Astronaut.

members.name: Rap Monster
members.history: Kim Nam-joon (Korean: 김남준; born September 12, 1994), known professionally as RM (formerly Rap Monster), is a South Korean rapper, songwriter, and record producer. He is the leader of South Korean boy band BTS.

members.name: Jisoo
members.history: Kim Ji-soo (Korean: 김지수; born January 3, 1995), known mononymously as Jisoo, is a South Korean singer and actress. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, formed by YG Entertainment, in August 2016. Outside of her music career, she made her acting debut with a cameo role in the 2015 series The Producers and played her first leading role in the JTBC series Snowdrop (2021–22).

members.name: Jennie
members.history: Jennie Kim (Korean: 김제니; born January 16, 1996), known mononymously as Jennie, is a South Korean singer, rapper, and actress. Born and raised in South Korea, Jennie studied in New Zealand for five years before returning to South Korea in 2010. She debuted as a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, formed by YG Entertainment, in August 2016. In 2023, she made her acting debut under the stage name Jennie Ruby Jane in the HBO television series The Idol.

members.name: Rosé
members.history: Roseanne Park MBE (born 11 February 1997), known mononymously as Rosé (Korean: 로제), is a Korean-New Zealand singer and dancer based in South Korea. Born in New Zealand and raised in Australia, Rosé signed with South Korean label YG Entertainment following a successful audition in 2012 and trained for four years before debuting as a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink in August 2016.

members.name: Lisa
members.history: Lalisa Manobal (also spelled Manoban; born Pranpriya Manobal; March 27, 1997), known mononymously as Lisa (Korean: 리사), is a Thai rapper, singer and dancer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, which debuted under YG Entertainment in August 2016. She is set to make her acting debut in 2025 in the HBO television series The White Lotus.

members.name: Miyeon
members.history: Cho Mi-yeon (Korean: 조미연; born January 31, 1997), better known mononymously as Miyeon, is a South Korean singer and actress. She is the vocalist of the South Korean girl group (G)I-dle under Cube Entertainment, and voiced Ahri in the virtual K-pop girl group K/DA.

members.name: Minnie
members.history: Nicha Yontararak (Thai: ณิชา ยนตรรักษ์; born October 23, 1997), better known by her nickname and stage name Minnie (Korean: 민니; Thai: มินนี่), is a Thai singer, and actress based in South Korea. She is a member of South Korean girl group (G)I-dle, which debuted on May 2, 2018 under Cube Entertainment.

members.name: Soyeon
members.history: Jeon So-yeon (Korean: 전소연; born August 26, 1998), known mononymously as Soyeon, is a South Korean rapper and record producer under Cube Entertainment. She first gained attention for competing in the television shows Produce 101 and Unpretty Rapstar before debuting as a solo artist on November 5, 2017. On May 2, 2018, she debuted as the leader and rapper of the girl group (G)I-dle, for whom she has written and produced most title songs. She is also part of SM Station X girl group project Station Young and has portrayed League of Legends character Akali in the virtual musical groups K/DA and True Damage.

members.name: Yuqi
members.history: Song Yuqi (Chinese: 宋雨琦, Korean: 송우기; born September 23, 1999), known mononymously as Yuqi (Korean: 우기), is a Chinese singer-songwriter, dancer and record producer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group (G)I-dle, which debuted under Cube Entertainment in May 2018. She has been a cast member of the Chinese variety show Keep Running since 2019 and hosted the KakaoTV reality show Learn Way (2020–2021). In May 2021, Yuqi made her solo debut with single album A Page.

members.name: Shuhua
members.history: Shuhua (슈화), also known as Yeh Shu Hua (葉舒華), is a Taiwanese singer under CUBE Entertainment. She is the vocalist, visual and maknae of the South Korean girl group (G)I-dle.

members.name: Changbin
members.history: Changbin (창빈 changbin) was born on August 11, 1999 (age 24) in Yongin, South Korea. He is a main rapper and producer (lyrics, composition) of the group Stray Kids.

members.name: Seungmin
members.history: Seungmin (승민 seungmin) was born on September 22, 2000 (age 23) in Seoul, South Korea. He is the main vocalist of the group Stray Kids.

members.name: Felix
members.history: Felix Yongbok Lee (born 15 September 2000), known mononymously as Felix, is an Australian rapper and singer based in South Korea. He is a member of the South Korean boy band Stray Kids, formed by JYP Entertainment in 2017.

members.name: Han
members.history: HAN (한 han) was born on September 14, 2000 (age 23) in Incheon, South Korea. He is a main rapper, producer (lyrics, composition) and vocalist of the group Stray Kids.

members.name: Hyunjin
members.history: Hyunjin (현진 hyeonjin) was born on March 20, 2000 (age 24) in Seoul, South Korea. He is a main dancer, rapper and visual of the group Stray Kids.

members.name: Lee Know
members.history: Lee Know (리노 rino) was born on October 25, 1998 (age 25) in Gimpo, South Korea. He is a main dancer, vocalist, rapper and visual of the group Stray Kids.

members.name: Bang Chan
members.history: Bang Chan (방찬 bangchan) was born on October 3, 1997 (age 26) in Seoul, South Korea. He is the leader and a producer (lyrics, composition, arrangement), vocalist and dancer of the group Stray Kids.

members.name: In
members.history: I.N (Korean: 아이엔; Japanese: アイエン) is a South Korean singer-songwriter and actor under JYP Entertainment. He is the maknae of the boy group Stray Kids.

members.name: Jihyo
members.history: Park Ji-hyo (Korean: 박지효; born Park Ji-soo, February 1, 1997), known mononymously as Jihyo, is a South Korean singer. She is the leader and vocalist of the South Korean girl group Twice, formed by JYP Entertainment in 2015.

members.name: Nayeon
members.history: Im Na-yeon[a] (Korean: 임나연; born September 22, 1995), known mononymously as Nayeon, is a South Korean singer. She rose to prominence as a member of the South Korean girl group Twice, created by JYP Entertainment through the reality television show Sixteen (2015).

members.name: Jeongyeon
members.history: Jeongyeon was born as Yoo Kyung-wan on 1 November 1996 in Suwon, Gyeonggi Province, South Korea. She has two older sisters, one of whom is the actress Gong Seung-yeon. Her father was a chef who worked for Kim Dae-jung, a former president of South Korea.

members.name: Momo
members.history: Momo Hirai (Japanese: 平井 もも, Hepburn: Hirai Momo, born November 9, 1996), known mononymously as Momo (Korean: 모모; Japanese: モモ), is a Japanese singer, rapper, and dancer based in South Korea. She is a member of South Korean girl group Twice under JYP Entertainment.

members.name: Sana
members.history: Sana Minatozaki (Japanese: 湊﨑 紗夏, Hepburn: Minatozaki Sana, born December 29, 1996), known mononymously as Sana (Korean: 사나; Japanese: サナ), is a Japanese singer based in South Korea. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Twice, formed in 2015 by JYP Entertainment.

members.name: Mina
members.history: Mina trained in ballet from a young age, having practiced it for eleven years before debuting with Twice. She attended Obayashi Sacred Heart School in Takarazuka, Hyōgo until 2013. She did not graduate because she moved to South Korea to become a trainee.

members.name: Dahyun
members.history: Kim Da-hyun (Korean: 김다현; born May 28, 1998), known mononymously as Dahyun, is a South Korean singer, rapper and actress. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Twice, formed by JYP Entertainment in 2015.

members.name: Chaeyoung
members.history: Chaeyoung was born in Seoul, South Korea on April 23, 1999. She took interest in performing arts from a young age and used to model for a children's magazine. Chaeyoung decided she wanted to become a singer before joining JYP Entertainment and took dance lessons for over one year.

members.name: Tzuyu
members.history: Tzuyu was born on June 14, 1999, in the East District of Tainan, Taiwan. She started dancing from a young age and trained at a dance academy. In 2012, Tzuyu was discovered by talent scouts at the Muse Performing Arts Workshop in Tainan, and moved to South Korea in November of that year to begin training.

members.name: Yeji
members.history: Hwang Ye-ji (Korean: 황예지; born May 26, 2000), known mononymously as Yeji (Korean: 예지), is a South Korean dancer and singer. She is the leader of the South Korean girl group Itzy, formed by JYP Entertainment in 2019.

members.name: Lia
members.history: Choi Ji-su, known mononymously as Lia (Korean: 리아), is a South Korean singer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Itzy.

members.name: Ryujin
members.history: Shin Ryu-jin (Korean: 신류진; born April 17, 2001), known mononymously as Ryujin (Korean: 류진), is a South Korean rapper, singer, and dancer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Itzy, formed by JYP Entertainment, in 2019.

members.name: Chaeryeong
members.history: Lee Chae-ryeong (Korean: 이채령; born June 5, 2001), known mononymously as Chaeryeong (Korean: 채령), is a South Korean singer and dancer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Itzy, formed by JYP Entertainment in 2019.

members.name: Yuna
members.history: Shin Yu-na (Korean: 신유나; born December 9, 2003), known mononymously as Yuna (Korean: 유나) is a South Korean dancer, rapper and singer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Itzy, formed by JYP Entertainment in 2019.

members.name: Minji
members.history: Minji was born Kim Min-ji on May 7, 2004 in Chuncheon, Gangwon, South Korea. During her elementary school years, she learned English before studying abroad in Canada for a few months.

members.name: Hanni
members.history: Hanni was born on October 6, 2004, in Melbourne, Australia. Her father and mother are Vietnamese. Her parents and grandparents emigrated to Australia some time before her birth. Her younger sister Jasmine was also born in Melbourne in 2007.

members.name: Danielle
members.history: Danielle June Marsh (born 11 April 2005), known mononymously as Danielle (Korean: 다니엘), is a Korean-Australian singer. She started out her career in the entertainment industry by making several appearances on television as a child, before debuting as a member of South Korean girl group NewJeans in 2022. The following year, Marsh ventured into acting, voicing Ariel in the Korean dub of the live-action adaptation of The Little Mermaid (1989).

members.name: Haerin
members.history: Haerin was born Kang Hae-rin on May 15, 2006 in Seoul, South Korea. Haerin attended school until her second year of middle school in 2020, during which she dropped out to become a trainee.

members.name: Hyein
members.history: Hyein (혜인) is a South Korean singer under ADOR. She is the maknae of the girl group NewJeans. She is also a former member of the kids co-ed group Play With Me Club and the kids girl group U.SSO Girl.

members.name: Jungwon
members.history: Jeongwon (정원) is a South Korean singer under Belift Lab. He is the leader of the boy group ENHYPEN. Born on February 9, 2004 in Gangnam-gu province, Seoul.

members.name: Heeseung
members.history: Lee Hee-seung (Hangul: 이희승, Japanese: イ・ヒスン), more well known by his stage name Heeseung (Hangul: 희승, Japanese: ヒスン), is a member of the South Korean boy group ENHYPEN. He was born on October 15, 2001 and is the center of the group.

members.name: Jay
members.history: Park Jae-beom (Korean 박재범, English Park Jae-beom; born April 25, 1987, Edmonds, Washington, USA), better known as Jay Park, is an American-Korean hip-hop artist and singer, dancer and music producer. Member of the Art of Movement breakdancing team based in Seattle. Founder and CEO of South Korean independent hip-hop labels AOMG and H1ghr Music. In August 2017, Park announced a partnership with Jay-Zs Roc Nation, becoming the first artist of Asian descent to sign to the label.

members.name: Jake
members.history: Shim Jake (Korean 심제이크, English Shim Jake; born November 15, 2002), also known as Shim Jae-Yun (Korean 심재윤, English Shim Jae-Yun) is a South Korean-Australian singer and rapper of Belift Lab. He is a member of the South Korean boy band Enhypen.

members.name: Sunghoon
members.history: Park Sunghoon (Korean: 박성훈, 朴成訓; born December 8, 2002, Namyangju, Gyeonggi) is a South Korean singer, emcee, and former figure skater. He is a member of the boy band Enhypen.

members.name: Sunoo
members.history: Kim Sunwoo (Korean: 김선우 born June 24, 2003. Better known as Sunwoo) is a South Korean singer and MC. Member of the K-pop boy band ENHYPEN.

members.name: Ni-ki
members.history: Nishimura Riki (Japanese 西村リキ, Korean 니시무라 리키, English Nishimura Riki; born December 9, 2005 in Okayama City, Okayama Prefecture, Japan), better known under the pseudonym Ni-Ki (Korean 니키 - read as Ni-Key) is a Japanese singer, dancer, and rapper from Belift Lab. The youngest member (maknae) of the South Korean boy band ENHYPEN.
